reviews.review: Well done Mr Abrams. A fitting end to the Skywalker Saga.

Falta de criatividade... usaram a mesma receita de bolo para criar um fã service bom, porem não e só isso que o fã quer, ele quer a maravilha que e Star Wars, um mundo imenso de possibilitadas! Porém J.J Abrams não quis inovar se prendeu ao básico dando oque alguns fãs queriam e assim arruinando o final da saga. 
Não, não e o pior filme... não e um fiasco... acho que J.J Abrão tivesse feito os 3 filmes da saga teria feito assim uma grande trilogia, espetacular... porem fez um ótimo primeiro dando a entrada para os próximos 2 diretores e após Disney não gostar do segundo decidiu devolver ao Abrão e assim teve que improvisar pois o segundo cortou milhares de possibilidades que ele poderia ter feito, tentando resumir assim 2 filmes em um só.
Good - not bad - but predictable and forgettable
This movie is everything that’s wrong with Hollywood and it’s over reliance on CGI when there’s no plot. JJ Abrams should be embarrassed of his effort or lack there of. AWFUL.

If you put all previous eight movies in a blender and then splattered it on the screen- thats what this movie was.  It closed all the loose ends but at a Helter Skelter pace.  I hope the future episodes can recapture the imagination of the fans in the way the original did.
enjoyed the movie like the facility

I had a lot of mixed judgement on this film and in order to rate it, I put all my criticism behind. As a stand-alone with no knowledge of the previous films, it would have delivered. It had Great CGI, Dynamic Backgrounds, funny Characters in a Sci-Fi world.  
As an Audience Review, it delivered.
As a Star Wars Fan - It was a mess. 
As a Child - It is unreal.

JJ Abrams proves that once again he has no fresh ideas. Rise of Skywalker is a vapid rehash of Return of the Jedi only with dropped plot threads, multiple nonsensical McGuffins, and a ludicrous plot that even manages to invalidate George Lucas' saga with its own through-line of the Chosen One and the sacrifices of the heroes.
A poorly paced, badly edited film that's only redeeming feature is the music by the legendary John Williams.
My expectations were exceeded! I really enjoyed the Rise of Skywalker.
